    <note>Kong(2) Yanzhou [24506] A rough translation of his entry in CBD is "He was appointed to a post in Dongping fu and had illicit sexual relations with an imperial clanswoman and, when the prefectural administrator, Quan(2) Bangyan [165], wanted to put a stop to it, Yanzhou led a multitude to Nanjing (i.e. Songzhou). He was appointed pacification officer for Qihuang Zhen (i.e. the Hupei-Hunan area) and then snatched the wife, born Zhao(1), of the Tanzhou (modern Changsha) vice prefect (Tongpan), Zhang(1) Zhan (not in dataset), who was also an imperial clanswoman, and carried madam Zhao(1) off with him when he abandoned his post and fled. He surrendered to the puppet state of Qi and then to Jin." He has entries in both the Song Shi xinbian and the Jinshi. CBD, 1, 394.</note>
